 🧭 Virtual Browser CI/CD Pipeline

This project sets up a **browser-in-browser** containerized application using [Neko](https://github.com/m1k1o/neko), with a full **CI/CD pipeline** powered by Jenkins, Docker, SonarQube, Trivy, and Docker Compose.

🚀 Features

- 🔍 Vulnerability scanning with Trivy (filesystem + Docker image)
- 🧪 Code quality analysis with SonarQube
- 🐳 Docker image build, tag, and push to Docker Hub
- 📦 Deployment using Docker Compose
- ✅ Automated pipeline via Jenkins

📁 Project Structure

. ├── .docker/ │ └── firefox/ # Dockerfile for Neko Firefox container ├── docker-compose.yaml # Compose file for deployment ├── Jenkinsfile # CI/CD pipeline definition └── README.md # You're here!


🛠️ Setup Instructions

 1. Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/<your-repo>.git
cd <your-repo>

2. Configure Jenkins
Install Jenkins (Docker recommended)

Install plugins: Pipeline, Docker Pipeline, SonarQube Scanner, Git

Add credentials:

DockerHub (docker-cred)

SonarQube server (sonar)

Create a Jenkins job pointing to this repo

3. Pull Required Docker Images

docker pull sonarqube:latest
docker pull aquasec/trivy:latest
docker pull nurdism/neko:firefox

🧪 Pipeline Stages
Git Checkout – Pulls latest code from GitHub

Trivy Filesystem Scan – Scans source files for vulnerabilities

SonarQube Analysis – Runs static code analysis

Docker Build & Tag – Builds image from Dockerfile

Trivy Docker Scan – Scans built image for vulnerabilities

Docker Push – Pushes image to DockerHub

Deploy – Uses Docker Compose to run the container

🔐 Login Credentials
By default, login is disabled for public access. To enable password protection, add these to docker-compose.yaml:

environment:
  NEKO_PASSWORD: yourpassword
  NEKO_PASSWORD_ADMIN: youradminpassword

📦 Deployment
docker-compose down -v
docker-compose up -d --build
Access the app at: http://localhost:8081

🧹 Cleanup
bash
docker image prune -f
docker-compose down -v
